		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/08/29/technology/circuits/29PHON.html">NYT article</a> describes that what we did by going to cellular may be a new trend: <i>Nearly 3 percent of telephone users have made wireless phones their primary telephone</i>.

So we only need a land line for TiVo, but <a href="http://pvrhack.sonnik.com/tivo/howto/tivo-dsl.htm">this HOWTO</a> describes how to make TiVo update itself over an internet connection instead of dialing out. This could save us $30/mo.]]></content:encoded>
